MusGlyphs is a font that makes it easier to type a wide variety of musical symbols directly into a word processor, combined with text fonts, without needing to adjust baselines or point sizes, like this:
The complex 6/8 + 2/4 signature has been replaced by six bars of 5/4 time High voice available in T3b and low voice in B2#
Swing rhythm is represented as e.s = qe3 at a dynamic range mp > ff Jazz musicians read shorthand like |LLL%LL|LLL%%LL| to play repeats
MusGlyphs modifies glyphs taken from Bravura and Academico and adjusts their position- ing.
MusGlyphs works in any word processor or other software that supports ligatures and kerning. Make sure these features are turned on for the glyphs to display correctly.
